                  <musicNotation>
                     <p>Several parts have indication of music given in neumes. These consisted of a
                        series of symbols drawn above the text, showing pitch direction and vocal
                        ornament. Neumes was used in the early Middle Ages and preceded the present
                        musical notation.</p>
                  </musicNotation>
                  <additions>
                     <p>A parchment flyleaf added subsequently to the text carries a four-line
                        erotic poem in Latin (from the <date notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699"
                           >seventeenth century</date>).</p>
                     <p>Marginalia in Icelandic occur on fols 1r, 15v, 16r and 115v; marginalia in
                        Latin occur on fols 40r, 54r, 97r and 106v.</p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="unknown">
